32:18.922 --> 32:21.527
Why would she do that? Why would
she come to you with that?

32:21.560 --> 32:22.930
She thinks you're so good
at lying that it's impossible

32:22.963 --> 32:24.901
to know when
you're telling the truth.

32:28.874 --> 32:30.511
MAN:
How was it?

32:30.545 --> 32:34.419
No, no, no, don't turn around,
not yet. No.

32:34.452 --> 32:36.857
Drink is not half bad.

32:36.890 --> 32:39.129
I never had one before.
What do you call it?

32:39.162 --> 32:42.802
A mai tai.
It was invented by Trader Vic,

32:42.835 --> 32:44.539
and it was so popular
in the '40s

32:44.573 --> 32:45.909
there was a shortage of rum.

32:45.943 --> 32:48.047
I can believe it.

32:48.080 --> 32:51.486
I usually have a bad reaction
to rum, but not to this.

32:54.025 --> 32:55.861
(gurgling)

32:55.896 --> 32:57.599
GINO:
Why are you pretending?

32:57.632 --> 32:59.569
-What are you hiding?
-(screaming)

33:01.873 --> 33:03.711
-Somebody call an ambulance.
-Move. Move, move!

33:03.744 --> 33:05.848
-Did anybody see what happened?
-BARTENDER: No. One minute,

33:05.881 --> 33:07.452
-he was sitting at the bar,
and the next...
-All right, all right,

33:07.485 --> 33:08.989
all right.
Just tell your boss to seal off

33:09.022 --> 33:10.993
all the exits.
Nobody comes in or out. Go. Now.

33:11.026 --> 33:13.731
Move. Go! Move!

33:13.764 --> 33:17.438
♪ Walk the night,
hey, gonna walk the night. ♪

33:29.162 --> 33:30.999
-(meowing)
-Okay, sweetie.

33:31.033 --> 33:32.735
There's a big bowl of warm milk

33:32.769 --> 33:35.441
and crème de cacao
for you at my place, okay?

33:35.474 --> 33:37.612
I think she's more
of a hard whiskey kind of gal.

33:37.645 --> 33:39.816
-(laughs)
-Why'd you have to bring her
home with you anyway?

33:39.849 --> 33:41.820
Oh, I have a thing
for lost souls.

33:41.853 --> 33:44.225
Well, there's about a thousand
lost souls right there,

33:44.259 --> 33:45.761
counting the fleas.

33:45.795 --> 33:47.131
(chuckles)

33:47.165 --> 33:48.969
It's probably all over me,
too, right now.

33:49.002 --> 33:50.538
I'll pick up a couple
of flea collars on the way

33:50.571 --> 33:51.873
and a muzzle for you.

33:51.908 --> 33:53.210
Sue me for telling it
like it is.

33:53.243 --> 33:55.081
Well, sue me for wanting someone

33:55.114 --> 33:56.985
-who'll be there
every time I get home.
-(low growling)

33:57.018 --> 33:59.189
-(yowls)
-What is your problem?

34:00.791 --> 34:03.030
Probably just smelled a dog
or something.

34:03.063 --> 34:04.733
You would know.

34:10.011 --> 34:13.651
HANNAH:
The patient, comma,
Mr. Whitely, comma,

34:13.684 --> 34:16.189
claims he noticed the lesion
on his foot a week ago.

34:16.223 --> 34:18.260
Period. Paragraph.

34:18.293 --> 34:21.466
I removed a small scraping
for analysis,

34:21.500 --> 34:25.141
but I believe it's another case
of Kaposi's sarcoma. Period.

34:25.174 --> 34:28.781
Before this year, Kaposi's were
mostly found in Italian men

34:28.814 --> 34:31.853
in their 70s, comma,
but suddenly, I'm seeing them...

34:31.887 --> 34:33.557
(phone ringing)

34:38.567 --> 34:40.071
Hello?

34:40.104 --> 34:42.208
FRAN:
Is this Dr. Hannah Wells?

34:42.241 --> 34:44.879
HANNAH:
Yes. Who am I speaking with?

34:44.914 --> 34:46.951
FRAN:
I know what's happening
to your patients, Dr. Wells.

34:46.984 --> 34:49.656
And I know what's happening
to the deer on Fire Island.

34:49.689 --> 34:51.827
HANNAH:
Tell me who this is.

34:51.860 --> 34:54.599
FRAN:
Meet me at the equestrian
statue in Central Park.

35:06.123 --> 35:08.160
(chains rattle in distance)

35:25.896 --> 35:27.532
Hey, hey, hey.
Take it easy.

35:27.565 --> 35:29.569
I thought I saw someone.

35:29.602 --> 35:31.974
He... he was right over there.

35:32.008 --> 35:35.047
(sighs) Are you the person
that called me?

35:35.081 --> 35:36.850
Yes. I'm Fran.

35:36.883 --> 35:38.554
Tell me what the hell
this is about.

35:38.587 --> 35:40.725
This is about a group
of people in this city,

35:40.758 --> 35:43.063
vulnerable people.

35:43.097 --> 35:44.799
They're under attack.

35:44.833 --> 35:46.803
Under attack? By whom?

35:46.837 --> 35:49.109
The U. S. government.

35:51.379 --> 35:53.584
(elevator bell dings)

36:06.911 --> 36:08.948
♪ ♪

36:36.670 --> 36:38.975
(door squeaks)

36:51.032 --> 36:53.036
-(door opens)
-(chains rattling)

36:55.909 --> 36:58.680
STEWART:
Get me the fuck out of here.

36:58.714 --> 37:00.284
Keep screaming like that,

37:00.317 --> 37:02.755
you're gonna fuck up
that perfect little throat.

37:06.263 --> 37:08.200
Hey, hey, hey.

37:08.233 --> 37:11.339
If I told you once,
I've told you a dozen times.

37:11.373 --> 37:14.045
It only hurts if you fight it.

37:14.078 --> 37:16.683
Where the hell were you?

37:16.716 --> 37:18.687
How could you just
leave me like this?

37:18.720 --> 37:20.090
Answer to question number one:

37:20.124 --> 37:22.930
none of your fucking business.

37:22.963 --> 37:26.369
Answer to question number two:

37:26.403 --> 37:28.841
how else did you want me
to leave you?

37:28.874 --> 37:30.344
-You're a sick fuck.
-I didn't do anything

37:30.377 --> 37:32.114
to you
you didn't absolutely love,

37:32.148 --> 37:33.717
and we both know that.

37:33.750 --> 37:35.454
-Well, I'm done.
-Oh.

37:35.487 --> 37:38.694
You're done
when I say you're done.

37:38.727 --> 37:40.731
(laughing)

37:42.235 --> 37:44.038
No, no.

37:44.072 --> 37:47.078
Stewie, baby,
you're just getting started.

37:47.111 --> 37:49.249
-(chains jangling)
-Let me out of here.

37:49.282 --> 37:51.786
Help!

37:51.820 --> 37:54.125
Somebody help me!

37:54.158 --> 37:56.062
Somebody!

37:56.096 --> 37:58.333
Please.
I didn't want this.

37:58.367 --> 38:00.371
I'm not enjoying it.

38:02.842 --> 38:04.412
You did answer a pay phone
on the street

38:04.445 --> 38:07.218
in front of a leather club,
did you not?

38:07.251 --> 38:10.291
So you knew exactly what
you were getting into, right?

38:10.324 --> 38:12.028
And you loved
every single second of it,

38:12.061 --> 38:13.830
didn't you, you little freak?

38:15.100 --> 38:17.104
You're fucking hot
when you're scared.

38:21.846 --> 38:23.450
Let's have some fun.

38:27.758 --> 38:30.030
(siren wailing in distance)

38:30.064 --> 38:32.101
(grunts softly)

38:50.037 --> 38:52.742
-I can't sleep.
-Neither can I.

38:52.775 --> 38:55.447
Yeah, why not-- all the noise?

38:55.481 --> 38:57.920
(chuckles): Noise?

38:57.953 --> 39:00.391
Nobody who grew up in the city
hears noise.

39:01.359 --> 39:02.428
No.

39:03.463 --> 39:04.934
It's the silence.

39:04.967 --> 39:07.171
It's everywhere.

39:08.240 --> 39:10.411
Oh, Jesus, Patrick.

39:10.444 --> 39:12.481
Another killing.

39:12.515 --> 39:14.285
Few feet away from us.

39:14.319 --> 39:16.056
Cops show up, do nothing.

39:16.089 --> 39:18.193
A miniature paper umbrella
on the floor

39:18.226 --> 39:19.997
doesn't really
give us much to go on.

39:20.030 --> 39:22.802
Plus, there was no drugs
in his drink,

39:22.835 --> 39:25.741
unlike what happened
to you, so...

39:28.513 --> 39:30.451
Thank you
for saying it out loud.

39:31.486 --> 39:34.492
We still haven't
really talked about it.

39:34.525 --> 39:37.431
Just more silence.

39:37.465 --> 39:39.202
As if it never happened.

39:39.235 --> 39:41.473
That terrifies me.

39:43.276 --> 39:46.049
'Cause you know
what all this quiet means?

39:47.885 --> 39:50.024
Secrets.

39:52.128 --> 39:54.866
You're the quietest one of all.

39:57.104 --> 39:59.342
(phone ringing)

40:01.613 --> 40:03.183
PATRICK:
Yeah.

40:03.216 --> 40:05.821
Okay, I'll be right there.

40:10.230 --> 40:11.533
They found something.

40:11.566 --> 40:13.804
♪ ♪

40:34.579 --> 40:36.883
(indistinct chatter)

40:36.917 --> 40:38.487
MAZARA:
All right, that makes sense.
Thank you.

40:38.520 --> 40:40.524
Hey, Chief, what's going on?

40:40.557 --> 40:42.294
Hey. So, uh,
you might have been right.

40:42.328 --> 40:44.298
Looks like your faggot killer
left us something new.

40:44.332 --> 40:46.169
Where's the body?

40:46.202 --> 40:48.173
Actually, we didn't
get a main course.

40:48.206 --> 40:49.542
We got an assortment.

40:49.575 --> 40:51.613
(camera shutter clicking)

40:54.685 --> 40:56.456
Holy shit.

40:56.489 --> 40:58.160
Looks like each one
is from a different victim.

